textAfterTable: 16 Songs Biography Born: August 8, 1920 in Gurdon, AR Genre: Blues Years Active: '40s, '50s, '60s, '70s, '80s, '90s One of the great blues singers of the post-World War II period, Jimmy Witherspoon was also versatile enough to fit comfortably into the jazz world. Witherspoon was born on August 8, 1920, in Gurdon, AR. As a child, he sang in a church choir, and made his debut recordings with Jay McShann for Philo and Mercury in 1945 and 1946.
